Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.49,0:01:35.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spear-wielder! Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.33,0:01:39.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't get away\Nlike you did before!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.00,0:01:41.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do everything in our\Npower to bring you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.73,0:01:45.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what your motive is,\Ndragging the prince around with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.13,0:01:47.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but your work is done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.07,0:01:50.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come out peacefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.04,0:01:54.54,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet, you noisy brats!\NWhat's all this shouting about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.19,0:02:04.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, isn't he...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.82,0:02:11.83,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 20\NTo Hunter's Hole
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.77,0:02:28.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You there. Are you a star reader?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.75,0:02:35.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am. Torogai, I wish that we had\Nhad the chance to meet sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.89,0:02:39.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the last thing I expected\Nto hear from a star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.69,0:02:42.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, now I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:48.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was you who had the second\Nqueen write a letter to me, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.50,0:02:49.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.43,0:02:53.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we might be able\Nto have a proper discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.44,0:02:59.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Young star reader, I want to hear\Nyour thoughts on this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.31,0:03:02.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.35,0:03:06.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your prince has been made\Nthe Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:09.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, when next year's\Nspring day of equality arrives...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.02,0:03:12.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...he will set out for a place\Ncalled the land of feasting...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.36,0:03:16.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...just like a migratory bird\Ntaking flight on its journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.73,0:03:23.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I have learned that an egg-eater\Nwill also come here from Nayug.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:24.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Egg-eater?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.20,0:03:30.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just like a brown bear coming\Nto feast on toburya...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:32.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that are swimming\Nupstream to spawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.14,0:03:37.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And according to Yakoo legends,\Nthe guardian of the spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:42.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is destined to be killed\Nby the egg-eater at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that\Nthe prince will die?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:48.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's what I'm saying!\NDon't make me repeat myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.13,0:03:56.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the extent of your knowledge\Nregarding the Nyunga Ro Chaga?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:02.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are there no stories about\Nthe guardian of the spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.84,0:04:06.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...escaping this fate in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.11,0:04:10.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, at least not in\NYakoo oral traditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.92,0:04:14.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Magic weaver of Yakoo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:18.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If what you say is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.02,0:04:21.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is it not all the more reason\Nto turn the prince over to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.36,0:04:25.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what sort of\Ncreature this "egg-eater" is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.90,0:04:29.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but the army of Yogo is\Nin excess of 10,000 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:34.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if a demon like the one described\Nin the official history should appear...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.47,0:04:37.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it will be a simple matter\Nfor us to defend the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:42.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will it still be a simple matter\Nif it's a monster from Nayug...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:46.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that can be neither seen\Nor touched by human beings?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.95,0:04:49.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To something from Nayug...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.99,0:04:55.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the walls and spearmen surrounding\Nyour palace won't mean a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.83,0:04:59.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hard you try\Nto hide the prince, in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.46,0:05:05.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it will reach out from Nayug with\Nits invisible claws and tear him apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.94,0:05:09.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knowing this, are you still telling me\Nthat you'll be able to do anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.34,0:05:11.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to stop the egg-eater\Nif we give him to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:20.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have access to the epitaphs left\Nby the original master star reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.12,0:05:23.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we can read and\Ndecipher them, perhaps we...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.12,0:05:28.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What the... You've had something\Nthat important all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.72,0:05:31.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and you haven't\Neven read it all yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.73,0:05:35.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That insolent whelp Hibi Tonan\Nmust have gone senile.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.10,0:05:41.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This proves we can't hand over the\Nprecious Nyunga Ro Chaga to that nitwit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.77,0:05:45.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that the Yakoo\Ncan protect him, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:46.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.44,0:05:49.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the spear-wielder...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.51,0:05:53.12,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...has already taken the\Nprince to a secret location.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.85,0:05:58.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I'm lying, feel free to\Nsearch the village from top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.33,0:06:07.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you must understand that she isn't\Nsimply refusing to hand over the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.33,0:06:10.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It just means that she wants to\Nprotect both the prince and the egg.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.77,0:06:13.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you people want\Nto save the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.94,0:06:16.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...go back and read\Nthose epitaphs or whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:20.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and come meet us at the land of\Nfeasting on the spring day of equality!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.34,0:06:22.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We will be waiting for you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:30.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of this! Prince Chagum\Nis our prince of Yogo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.52,0:06:35.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll protect him ourselves!\NWe don't need help from you Yakoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.49,0:06:40.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you cut down\Neveryone in this village?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.83,0:06:44.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you think that will save your\Nprince and this land, then do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.07,0:06:48.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if you blindly\Nreturn with the prince...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.34,0:06:50.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...the Nayug creature will\Nfollow you to the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.04,0:06:55.01,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Pointless slaughter\Nwill accomplish nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:56.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put away your swords!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.28,0:07:01.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai, it would appear\Nthat we star readers...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.92,0:07:04.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...have become quite\Narrogant over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:09.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to your people,\Nour knowledge is sorely lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:13.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your men don't seem to\Nbe of the same opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.26,0:07:18.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I will leave\Nthis place with my men.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.17,0:07:22.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But by the time of the\Nspring day of equality...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:25.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I will find a way to save Prince\NChagum, and we will surely return here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.14,0:07:29.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When we do, I expect that you\Nwill return Prince Chagum to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:30.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.51,0:07:31.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Silence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:35.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You tried with all your might, and\Nstill you couldn't kill this bodyguard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.82,0:07:41.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Entrusting the prince to her until\Nspring is the safest course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.33,0:07:47.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jin, perhaps what\NMaster Shuga says is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.66,0:07:49.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, put away your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:58.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Magic weaver,\Nis His Highness in good health?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:13.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Torogai, let us meet\Nagain in the land of feasting next spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.04,0:08:30.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you Torogai's apprentice?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.68,0:08:33.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:36.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your\Nassistance that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.98,0:08:41.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your information regarding mantis\Neggs was the key that led me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:43.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:52.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't a moment to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.93,0:08:54.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as we\Nreturn to the palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.60,0:08:57.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I must organize a team\Nto read through the epitaphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.60,0:09:01.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He remembered me. I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:05.17,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've met that star reader before?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.47,0:09:09.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, once. On the outskirts\Nof Ogi no Shimo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.95,0:09:12.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit, Torogai...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:15.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I'm amazed you managed to\Ncome up with a lie like that on the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.02,0:09:20.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once Balsa gets back,\Nwe'll set out for Hunter's Hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.67,0:10:44.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure that\Nyou can't stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:45.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.44,0:10:51.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There are certain preparations\Nthat I want the boy to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:53.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.08,0:10:56.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for helping us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.35,0:11:00.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have no intention of\Nspending the winter idly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.06,0:11:03.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the Nyunga Ro Chaga to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We are all counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.07,0:11:15.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is shikul honey\Nthat Nimka collected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.47,0:11:18.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please enjoy it while you\Nare holed up in the cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:28.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:36.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.33,0:11:43.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.27,0:11:47.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:13.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? They're seeing us off?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.31,0:12:26.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are they bowing for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:29.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They do it to show their\Nrespect toward the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.98,0:12:33.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who shoulders the destiny\Nthat someone had to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:13:02.04,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.15,0:13:10.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.33,0:13:23.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.30,0:13:27.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.07,0:13:32.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:36.18,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai is currently...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.18,0:13:38.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's all right. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.28,0:13:43.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon the interruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:50.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.33,0:13:54.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have come because\NI wish to ask for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.80,0:13:59.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With Crown Prince Sagum dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.30,0:14:02.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I have been removed from\Nmy post of tutor-governor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.60,0:14:04.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,While you, on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.91,0:14:09.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...now hold authority on par with\Nthe master star reader himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.18,0:14:12.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That being the case,\Nwhy not simply give me an order?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.75,0:14:16.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I have no right to refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.59,0:14:22.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai,\NI travelled to Toumi village.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.49,0:14:24.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There, I learned to my chagrin...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:27.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that star readers' knowledge pales\Nin comparison to that of the Yakoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.70,0:14:32.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, we must now\Nsurpass even their knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:35.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't concern me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.64,0:14:40.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I beg to differ.\NThis concerns not only Shin-Yogo...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.58,0:14:44.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but everyone who lives\Non the Nayoro peninsula!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:49.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai, do me\Nthe honor of assisting me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:52.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...by taking charge of our\Nepitaph-deciphering efforts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.72,0:14:56.16,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are conversant in\Nevery field of knowledge...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:14:58.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and you possess a\Ndeeply inquisitive mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.93,0:15:02.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only one man is capable of keeping\Nthis project running smoothly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.83,0:15:05.70,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai, that man is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.43,0:15:40.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This area is colder\Nthan it is in Kosenkyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:42.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...so the leaves\Nchange color much earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.15,0:16:00.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's been like that\Never since we left Toumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.99,0:16:05.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but at least we're\Nalmost at Hunter's Hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.63,0:16:09.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll worry about Chagum\Nafter we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.27,0:16:11.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.11,0:16:24.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I swear, you leave this place vacant\Nfor a while and look what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.69,0:16:36.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai and I made\Na few improvements...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:39.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...in the cavern here\Nbeneath the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.23,0:16:42.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait here. We'll go light some fires.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.21,0:16:57.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Jiguro...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.68,0:16:59.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.88,0:17:04.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we've got some lights going!\NTry making your way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.89,0:17:14.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get him to hold\Nhis head high like he used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:23.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised? We call this part\Nof the cave the entry hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.07,0:17:28.31,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it's too open and cold out here,\Nso we set up the rooms further in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:29.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.15,0:17:36.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The hole on the right extends so far that\Nit's like a maze, so don't go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.75,0:17:41.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a spring in the middle one.\NThe one on the left is our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.43,0:17:44.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.46,0:17:49.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over there is a room where\Nwe smoke meats or whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.36,0:17:52.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over there is the storehouse\Nfor supplies and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.83,0:17:55.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There doesn't seem to be\Nany obvious damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.94,0:17:59.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This place never changes, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:02.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Every last detail is\Nexactly like it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:06.75,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time I've been\Nback here since Jiguro died.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.38,0:18:10.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be penned in here\Nonce it starts snowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.82,0:18:15.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's a lot that we\Nneed to see to before then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:18.53,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get ready to\Nhole up for the winter right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:50.43,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You give it a try too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:54.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't prepare them like this,\Nthey won't smoke properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.50,0:19:04.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I think I'll go\Nmake us some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.51,0:19:12.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once we're done with these,\Nwe'll turn in early.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.12,0:19:16.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going out first thing\Nin the morning to set traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.42,0:19:19.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.04,0:19:43.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You clean it just like\Nyou would a hare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.01,0:19:45.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Give it a try on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.57,0:20:06.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This place is pretty much full.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.90,0:20:09.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This should be more than enough\Nto keep us fed through winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.38,0:20:18.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda, do you have\Nany insect galls?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.21,0:20:20.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to tan some hides.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.42,0:20:22.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.22,0:20:28.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to borrow this\Nmortar and pestle too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.06,0:20:30.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.73,0:20:33.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa, is this enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.40,0:20:36.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be plenty. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.40,0:20:46.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks to me like that boy\Nhas toughened up quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.41,0:20:51.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's enduring\NBalsa's tough training too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:54.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, but I'm worried that\Nhe hardly ever says anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.52,0:20:59.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has to work that\Nthrough on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.56,0:21:03.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We can try to talk to him as\Nmuch as we want, but in the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.99,0:21:09.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...it's the boy who has to accept\Nthe fate of the Nyunga Ro Chaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:19.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.54,0:21:22.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.71,0:21:27.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your hand is chapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.62,0:21:30.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, I'll put some salve on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.76,0:21:45.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there. This medicine\Nmight sting, but it works wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.57,0:21:52.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Back when I was your age,\Nmy hands were rubbed raw a lot too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.61,0:21:56.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And every time, Jiguro rubbed\Nthis salve on them for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.08,0:21:58.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was usually very strict...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.98,0:22:02.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but whenever my hands were chapped,\Nhe became gentle for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.52,0:22:07.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This Jiguro person...\NWas he the man who raised you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.02,0:22:13.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he was my foster father,\Nand the man I owe my life to.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.93,0:22:16.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The man you owe your life to?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.40,0:22:18.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.13,0:22:22.94,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I never\Ndid tell you about him, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.34,0:22:29.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for Jiguro,\NI probably wouldn't be here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.61,0:22:33.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I would have been killed\Nwhen I was six, no question.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.02,0:22:39.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you tell me about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.82,0:22:45.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, maybe this is\Nthe right time to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.56,0:22:49.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you know,\Nmy homeland of Kanbal...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.66,0:22:54.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...is a small country that lies\Nbeyond the Misty Blue Mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.54,0:23:01.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even in a place like that, people\Nconstantly want to start conflicts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.21,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.98,0:24:46.11,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With pleading eyes,\Nhe begged his friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.12,0:24:48.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Look after my daughter," he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.68,0:24:51.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Jiguro Musa."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:56.99,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 21\NJiguro Musa
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.25,0:24:55.26,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I quit the King's Spears?
